p: \rI am Diana. Leader of the Selene City Gym.
\rThe Gym I run is themed around dreams- and as such, I specialize in both Psychic- and Ghost-types.
\rI hope you found my Gym puzzle clever.\nIf you understood the poem, I'm sure you had no trouble getting through my Gym at all.
\rWhen it said to walk right ahead... well, I couldn't be any more literal!
\rLet's get this show on the road. Get ready to lose!
\rIt seems as if I've been toppled...
\rI guess it had to happen eventually!
\rThis will let higher level Pokemon obey you.
\rIt can also attract rarer wild Pokemon in certain areas, such as the Friend Safari.
\rAnd take this, too, as a gift from me.
\rPsychic is perhaps the most well-known Psychic-type move.\nIt's very strong, and very reliable.
\rThis TM is definitely an invaluable asset for any trainer.
\rNext, I'll assume you'll want to go to Amphitrite City.
\rMy boyfriend, Calreath, runs the Gym there.\nHis team specializes around the Rain, so you might want to prepare for that.
\rOh, and don't forget- you can exit the Gym just by going straight down.
Welcome to the Gym of Dreams.
Where walls are sightless, and not is all as it seems.
Leave no stone unturned or unexplored.
So walk right on, hero, and find just reward.
A chance was taken, a chance was missed.
To not fight trainers and to persist.
But a chance you had and have again.
To walk straight into Her domain.

\bDiana here has themed her Gym around dreams. That way, she can use her two favourite types: Psychic and Ghost!
\bDark-types are your friend here, for sure.\nGhost-types too!
\bOh, and another thing. There's a lot of trainers here, but they don't give as much experience as you might want... that's because you're supposed to avoid them!
\bNicely done, champ, I can't believe you beat Diana. Great work!
